    "time_total_min": 40,
    "steps": [
      {
        "step_no": 1,
        "text": "Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C). Prepare pork by patting dry and seasoning all over with half the salt and pepper; let sit while you trim and halve the Brussels sprouts and toss them with olive oil, remaining salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes in a bowl.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Heat an oven-safe skillet over medium-high heat and add neutral oil. When shimmering, sear the pork tenderloin on all sides until deeply golden (about 2–3 minutes per side) to develop a crust.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Add halved Brussels sprouts to the skillet, arranging cut sides down around the pork. Transfer skillet to the preheated oven and roast until pork reaches 140°F (60°C) internal temperature and sprouts are tender with crisped edges.",
        "time_min": 12
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "While roasting, mix softened butter with minced garlic, chopped thyme, rosemary, lemon zest and juice. When pork is done, remove skillet from oven and transfer pork to a cutting board to rest for 6–8 minutes; tent loosely with foil.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Return skillet with sprouts to stovetop over medium heat for 1–2 minutes to reincorporate pan fond; stir in the garlic-herb butter to glaze the sprouts. Slice rested pork into medallions, arrange with Brussels sprouts, and sprinkle with grated parmesan if using before serving.",
        "time_min": 4
      }
